post_text:
Hello graduates!

We wanted to give you a follow up to the graduation packet that you received.

Friday, July 24th, we will hold graduation practice @ 5:00 on the football field.

Immediately following practice, there will be a short senior gathering that will take place outside right next to the football field. This is NOT mandatory; however you must enter at the start of the event (immediately following practice) if you would like to attend.

Masks WILL BE REQUIRED and proper social distancing WILL BE MANDATORY. You may bring a chair or blanket to sit on.

There will be a DJ and we will provide a few desserts and drinks. The senior video will be played for everyone between 7:30-8:00.

***If you leave the event after you check in, you will not be permitted to return***

Graduation: All graduates should wear a solid RED mask or RED Delsea mask with earloops (no gaiters). If you do not have one, you will be provided a red disposable face mask from the school.

Thank you to Mrs. Bilinski for sharing this awesome story about one of our SAVE students, Tyler, and one of our amazing paras in the SAVE program, Sue Coppola ‚ù§Ô∏è

___________________________________________

‚ÄúWe love bragging about our paras in the SAVE program!

Mrs. Susan Coppola FaceTimes with Tyler every. single. day! They check in, talk about their day, go over weather and upcoming events, and talk about Ty‚Äôs favorite subject ‚Äî cars! She even sends him a letter that he receives in the mail every single day. They read the letter together and she sends him pictures of classmates and memories of the SAVE Program from this year. Thank you, Mrs. Coppola!‚Äù

#delseapride!!!

post_text:
On Wednesday, May 20, Mrs. Bilinski and Mr. Flaim delivered hoagie making kits to the students in the SAVE Program!

This life-skills lesson was an excellent way for students to practice following directions and making a meal.

A big THANK YOU goes out to Heritages in Clayton for donating ALL of the kits for the program! Our students do volunteer work at Heritages during the school year in the school-to-work program.

We are so grateful for our relationship with Heritages and the opportunities they provide for our students! #delseapride!

Dance and sing along with your favorite strange family members including Wednesday (Emily Lancetta), Morticia (Taylor Carino), Gomez (Michael Mellor), and Uncle Fester (Joseph Hepler). In this performance, you are invited to Wednesday‚Äôs 18th birthday, which is when she announces her engagement to a boy from rural Ohio. Watch as the family falls apart, secrets get told, disclosures are shared, and drama ensues. Tickets go on sale February 24 for $14 each. Contact Christine Doughtery at 856-694-0100 x376 or at cdougherty@delsearegional.us for ticket sales. Tickets will also be sold at the door while supplies last. Show dates are March 12, 13, and 14. So grab your potions and flip the switch as you join us for a spectacular performance of The Addams Family.

post_text:
Students in Pam DeRose's AP Studio Art class participated in the Youth Art Month design contest titled, "Take A Journey Through Art."

There were over 250 student submissions throughout the state and Delsea's own Talia Metcalf was chosen as the winner.

Talia's design will be featured on the flag that will hang at the YAM Museum at the National Art Educators Convention in Minneapolis. In March,Talia will attend the State Youth Art Month reception in Trenton where she will receive her award.

"I have been making art my whole life, and from the beginning, my family and I knew it would be something special. Art can be a stress reliever for me and it boosts my confidence. It has shaped the person I am today and am proud of it. I‚Äôm thankful for everyone who has helped me along my journey and I can‚Äôt wait to see where it takes me next!" -Talia Metcalf, Delsea Regional High School, Grade 10

Congratulations, Talia!!! #delseapride!!!

Delsea Art Club visited the Barnes Museum on Friday, Dec 13 and had a private tour of the traveling "30 Americans" exhibit.

"30 Americans" showcases works by many of the most important African American artists of the last three decades.

This provocative exhibition focuses on issues of racial, sexual, and historical identity in contemporary culture while exploring the powerful influence of artistic legacy and community across generations.

On Saturday, December 14, the Delsea Regional High School FFA/Horticulture classes will be hosting their annual Winter Holiday Shopping Extravaganza. Vendors who are interested in participating should contact Gary Nelson (delseaffa@gmail.com) for a copy of the vendor form.

The show will run from 9 am until 4 pm; vendors can start their set up at 6 am. The fee is $30 for an 8' space and $50 for 16'. Payments for vendor spaces are due by Dec 10.

its annual "Toys For Tots" campaign to assist families in need.

If you or your student attend Delsea High School or Delsea Middle School and wish to donate, you can drop
off donations in the main lobby of the high school or middle school during normal school hours until Wednesday, December 19th.

We are in need of new toys for girls and boys ages toddler to teen. *New toys only, please.

Thank you for your support! #delseapride!!!
